The author expresses their support for the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act and urges the Senate to pass meaningful police reform legislation that holds law enforcement officers accountable. They acknowledge the efforts of Senator Cory Booker and Congresswoman Karen Bass in negotiating a bipartisan bill in the Senate. The author expresses disappointment in Senate Republicans for rejecting modest reforms and not addressing key issues. However, they remain hopeful for comprehensive police reform legislation and highlight the steps taken by their administration, such as new policies on chokeholds, no-knock warrants, and body cameras. They emphasize the importance of taking action and not allowing those who oppose progress to hinder their efforts. The author plans to continue working with lawmakers and consulting with civil rights and law enforcement communities to advance police reform. They also mention the possibility of further executive actions to promote equal justice under the law.